## Test-Specific Exercise Rules

### СЛУШАНЕ (Listening)

- `reading_text` with **`hideText: true`** — text hidden, TTS Play button per image
- Each image gets its own TTS button underneath (paragraphs[i] maps to images[i])
- **If no speaker images exist** (e.g. dialogue between multiple unnamed speakers): omit `images` array entirely; use a single paragraph with the full listening text — the component will show one global TTS button
- `true_false` with **`model`** — shows greyed-out example row before questions
- Instruction: `'Слушайте текста и отговорете на въпросите с ДА или НЕ.'`

### ЧЕТЕНЕ (Reading)

- `reading_text` with **`noTranslation: true`** — no click-to-speak, no InlineTranslation
- Students read the text themselves without AI assistance
- `workbook_fill_blank` with **`options` on every sentence** — always dropdown, never free text
- Each blank must have 3–4 distractor options from the same vocabulary domain

### ГРАМАТИКА (Grammar)

- **All `workbook_fill_blank` exercises MUST have `options`** — dropdown menus, not free text
- Verb conjugation: options = all 6 forms of the verb (аз/ти/той-тя/ние/вие/те)
- Numbers: options = 4 choices including the correct digit and plausible distractors (reversed digits, wrong magnitude)
- Verb "съм": options = `['съм', 'си', 'е', 'сме', 'сте', 'са']` for every sentence
- `word_order` and `multiple_choice` work the same as in lessons

#### Grammar context images

- `workbook_fill_blank` supports a single `imageUrl` field — shown above the sentences
- **If an exercise needs 2+ context images** (e.g. ЯМ + ПИЯ with two illustrations): insert a `reading_text` with `noTranslation: true` immediately BEFORE the `workbook_fill_blank`. Set `paragraphs: []` and list all images in the `images` array. The `workbook_fill_blank` itself gets no `imageUrl`.
- Context images live in `/public/assets/test-a1-N/gramatika/`

#### Dialogue ordering exercise

- **Use `workbook_fill_blank` (NOT `dialogue_builder`)** so it is scoreable
- First line is `isExample: true` (number 1, given to the student)
- Each remaining line gets a number dropdown: `options: ['2','3','4','5','6','7']`
- Instruction: `'Подредете диалога. Напишете номера на репликите в правилен ред.'`
- `layout: 'single'`, optional `imageUrl` for context photo

### ПИСАНЕ (Writing)

Two valid patterns depending on available images:

#### Pattern A — Individual images per puzzle (default, test-a1-1 style)
- `syllable_blocks` with **`imageUrl` per puzzle** and **`columns: 3`**
- Each puzzle card shows: image on top → scrambled letters below → green border on correct
- No separate `illustrated_cards` exercise — images are embedded in puzzles
- Single-word items: individual letter blocks (`['и', 'б', 'ц', 'а', 'н', 'а']`)
- Multi-word items: syllable blocks (`['ки', 'се', 'ло', 'мля', 'ко']`)
- No food labels shown — student must figure out the word from the image

#### Pattern B — Single shared scene image (test-a1-2 style, when only one image exists)
- Add a `reading_text` with `noTranslation: true` BEFORE the `syllable_blocks` — this shows the scene image prominently at the top (`paragraphs: []`, one image in `images` array)
- The `syllable_blocks` puzzles have **NO `imageUrl`** — only letter/syllable blocks are shown
- Instruction: e.g. `'Намерете продуктите в кошницата и наредете буквите, за да получите думата.'`
- Scrambled letter order must be **fixed** (not random): move the first letter/syllable to the end. Example: `'домат'` → `['о', 'м', 'а', 'т', 'д']`

## metadata.ts Rules

- `totalPoints` = sum of all section `maxPoints`
- `introText` is required — 2–3 sentences explaining what the test covers, which lessons, which components
- `introText` auto-translates via `useTranslate()` on the test page
- `title` format: `'Тест – уроци X, Y и Z'` or `'Тест – урок X'`

## index.ts Structure

```typescript
import type { TestData } from '@/content/types';
import { metadata } from './metadata';
import { listeningExercises, readingExercises, grammarExercises, writingExercises } from './exercises';

export const testData: TestData = {
  ...metadata,
  sections: [
    { id: 'listening', name: 'КОМПОНЕНТ СЛУШАНЕ', maxPoints: NN, exercises: listeningExercises },
    { id: 'reading',   name: 'КОМПОНЕНТ ЧЕТЕНЕ',  maxPoints: NN, exercises: readingExercises },
    { id: 'grammar',   name: 'КОМПОНЕНТ ГРАМАТИКА', maxPoints: NN, exercises: grammarExercises },
    { id: 'writing',   name: 'КОМПОНЕНТ ПИСАНЕ',  maxPoints: NN, exercises: writingExercises },
  ],
};

export default testData;
```

## Scoring & Results

The `TestScoreSummary` component ([src/components/TestScoreSummary.tsx](mdc:src/components/TestScoreSummary.tsx)) renders automatically at the bottom of every test page inside `LessonExercisesProvider`.

### How scores are calculated from saved state

| Exercise type | Saved state fields | Score formula |
|---|---|---|
| `true_false` | `{ answers, checked }` | Count where `(answer === 'true') === sentence.isTrue` |
| `workbook_fill_blank` | `{ answers, validation, isSubmitted }` | Count `validation[key] === true` |
| `multiple_choice` | `{ selectedAnswers, isSubmitted }` | Count `selectedAnswers[i] === correctIndex` |
| `word_order` | `{ questionStates, isSubmitted }` | Count `built.join(' ') === correctSentence` |
| `syllable_blocks` | `{ completed }` | Count `completed[id] === true` |

### 3 Performance Tiers

| Range | Color | Message (auto-translated via useTranslate) |
|---|---|---|
| 0–50% | 🔴 Red | "Нужна е още практика. Прегледайте **[label]** отново и обърнете внимание на по-слабите компоненти." |
| 51–75% | 🟡 Amber | "Добро начало! Имате основни познания, но трябва да упражнявате повече някои компоненти." |
| 76–100% | 🟢 Green | "Отлично! Справяте се много добре с материала от **[label]**. Продължавайте напред!" |

The `[label]` placeholder is extracted automatically from `testData.title` via `buildTierMessages()` inside `TestScoreSummary.tsx` — **no manual changes needed per test**.

### Per-component breakdown

- Progress bar + `earned/total` for each section with `maxPoints > 0`
- Sections below 50% are highlighted in red with a "needs more practice" hint
- Summary is **expanded by default** — students see the breakdown immediately
- **Appears as soon as ANY exercise state is saved** (not just after submission or earned points)

### Rules for new tests

- `totalPoints` in metadata MUST equal the sum of all section `maxPoints`
- Sections with `maxPoints: 0` are excluded from the scoring breakdown
- **Tier messages are automatic** — `buildTierMessages()` reads the lesson label from `testData.title`; no per-test configuration needed

## Test Content Quality (from feedback on tests A1.1–A1.3)

- **First word capitalized** — every sentence in grammar exercises, true_false, and word_order options must start with a capital letter.
- **Syllable scrambling** — in `syllable_blocks`, letters/syllables must be TRULY scrambled (not just slightly rearranged). Move first letter/syllable to end, then shuffle further.
- **Remove redundant instructions** — if the exercise is self-explanatory (e.g. only images with dropdowns), remove the instruction text.
- **Dialogue on new lines** — in `reading_text` containing dialogues, each reply = separate paragraph.
- **„Вярно/Грешно"** — use these instead of „Да/Не" for true_false questions about text comprehension.
- **Mixed true/false** — interleave correct and incorrect answers; never group all „Вярно" first.

## Automatic UI Behaviors (inherited from exercise components)

These are built into the exercise components and apply to tests automatically:

- **Options are shuffled** — `WorkbookFillBlank` shuffles `options[]` on render
- **Reset button** — All exercise components show a "Reset" button alongside "Check"
- **TTS** — Components use `speakBulgarian()` from `@/lib/tts` with automatic voice selection

## Creating Tests — ALWAYS Use Templates

When creating a new test, **always read `@TEST_TEMPLATES.ts` first**.
Copy the relevant section template and replace only the content.

## Registration Checklist

When adding a new test:
1. Create folder `src/content/tests/test-lessons-X-Y/`
2. Create `metadata.ts`, `exercises.ts`, `index.ts`
3. Copy images to `public/assets/test-a1-N/`
4. Add to `testFolderMap` in [src/content/index.ts](mdc:src/content/index.ts)
5. Verify `navItems` has the correct label
6. Verify `totalPoints` = sum of section `maxPoints`
